<p class="p">The moisture ratio (MR) of lavender leaves during drying experiments was calculated using the following equation:
 <disp-formula id="FD1-molecules-24-00764" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
  <math id="mm1" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">M</mi>
     <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">M</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mo class="mo">(</mo>
          <mi class="mi">t</mi>
          <mo class="mo">)</mo>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">M</mi>
        <mi class="mi">e</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">M</mi>
        <mi class="mi">o</mi>
       </msub>
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">M</mi>
        <mi class="mi">e</mi>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula> where M
 <sub class="sub">(t)</sub> is the moisture content at time τ. M
 <sub class="sub">o</sub> is the initial moisture content, and M
 <sub class="sub">e</sub> is the equilibrium moisture content (kg water/kg dry matter). The values of M
 <sub class="sub">e</sub> are relatively small comparing to those of M
 <sub class="sub">(t)</sub> or M
 <sub class="sub">o</sub>. The error due to the simplification is negligible [
 <xref rid="B46-molecules-24-00764" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">46</xref>,
 <xref rid="B47-molecules-24-00764" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">47</xref>,
 <xref rid="B48-molecules-24-00764" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">48</xref>], thus the moisture ratio was calculated as follows: 
 <disp-formula id="FD2-molecules-24-00764" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(2)</label>
  <math id="mm2" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi class="mi">M</mi>
     <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">M</mi>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mo class="mo">(</mo>
          <mi class="mi">t</mi>
          <mo class="mo">)</mo>
         </mrow>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msub class="msub">
        <mi class="mi">M</mi>
        <mn class="mn">0</mn>
       </msub>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
